#: ../../../versioning.rst:5
msgid "Versioning and API stability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:8
msgid "Versioning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:10
msgid "There are 3 numbers in a Scrapy version: *A.B.C*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:12
msgid ""
"*A* is the major version. This will rarely change and will signify very "
"large changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:14
msgid ""
"*B* is the release number. This will include many changes including features "
"and things that possibly break backward compatibility, although we strive to "
"keep these cases at a minimum."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:17
msgid "*C* is the bugfix release number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:19
msgid ""
"Backward-incompatibilities are explicitly mentioned in the :ref:`release "
"notes <news>`, and may require special attention before upgrading."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:22
msgid ""
"Development releases do not follow 3-numbers version and are generally "
"released as ``dev`` suffixed versions, e.g. ``1.3dev``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:26
msgid ""
"With Scrapy 0.* series, Scrapy used `odd-numbered versions for development "
"releases`_. This is not the case anymore from Scrapy 1.0 onwards."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:29
msgid ""
"Starting with Scrapy 1.0, all releases should be considered production-ready."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:31
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:33
msgid ""
"*1.1.1* is the first bugfix release of the *1.1* series (safe to use in "
"production)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:38
msgid "API stability"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:40
msgid "API stability was one of the major goals for the *1.0* release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:42
msgid ""
"Methods or functions that start with a single dash (``_``) are private and "
"should never be relied as stable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:45
msgid ""
"Also, keep in mind that stable doesn't mean complete: stable APIs could grow "
"new methods or functionality but the existing methods should keep working "
"the same way."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:53
msgid "Deprecation policy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:55
msgid ""
"We aim to maintain support for deprecated Scrapy features for at least 1 "
"year."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:57
msgid ""
"For example, if a feature is deprecated in a Scrapy version released on June "
"15th 2020, that feature should continue to work in versions released on June "
"14th 2021 or before that."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:61
msgid ""
"Any new Scrapy release after a year *may* remove support for that deprecated "
"feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../versioning.rst:64
msgid ""
"All deprecated features removed in a Scrapy release are explicitly mentioned "
"in the :ref:`release notes <news>`."
msgstr ""
